data.title: Body mass index is associated with biological CSF markers of core brain pathology of Alzheimer's disease
data.meta_description: Weight changes are common in aging and Alzheimer's disease (AD) and postmortem findings suggest a relation between lower body mass index (BMI) and increased AD brain pathology. In the current multicenter study, we tested whether lower BMI is associated with higher core AD brain pathology as assessed …
